#. type: Table
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"Whether HTTP/3 (QUIC) support is enabled.\n"
"When enabled and the native QUIC library is on the classpath, HTTP/3 is added to the set of supported HTTP versions on the HTTPS server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "`quarkus.http3.alt-svc`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"Whether to add the `Alt-Svc` response header to HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 responses on the HTTPS server, advertising HTTP/3 availability.\n"
"The header value follows the format `h3=\":PORT\"; ma=MAX_AGE`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "`quarkus.http3.alt-svc-max-age`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "Duration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "`24H`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"The `max-age` value included in the `Alt-Svc` header.\n"
"Tells clients how long to cache the HTTP/3 advertisement before re-checking via HTTP/1.1 or HTTP/2.\n"
"Only effective when `quarkus.http3.alt-svc` is `true`."
msgstr ""

