#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "When the HTTP/3 extension is on the classpath and no TLS configuration is detected, Quarkus auto-generates a certificate in dev and test mode:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"If the **Quarkus Dev CA** exists at `~/.quarkus/quarkus-dev-root-ca.pem`, the certificate is signed by it.\n"
"Browsers and clients that trust the Dev CA will accept the certificate without warnings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"Otherwise, a **self-signed certificate** is generated.\n"
"Browsers will show a certificate warning, which is acceptable for development."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "Run `quarkus tls generate-quarkus-ca --install` to create the Dev CA and install it in your system trust store for the best developer experience."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"When auto-TLS is active, plain HTTP requests are **redirected to HTTPS** by default.\n"
"To allow plain HTTP alongside HTTPS, set:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"In **production mode**, no auto-generation occurs.\n"
"If TLS is not configured, the server fails at startup with a clear error message."
msgstr ""

