#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "Automatic dependency selection (Maven only)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"When you add the `quarkus-http3` extension **with Maven**, the native QUIC library matching your **build-time** OS and architecture is included automatically using Maven profile activation.\n"
"No manual dependency configuration is needed for typical development and single-platform deployments."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "**Gradle does not support conditional profile activation.** Gradle users must always declare the native QUIC dependency manually — see <<gradle-quic-dependency>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "Adding additional platform dependencies (Maven)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "If you build on one platform but deploy to another (for example, building on macOS but deploying to Linux), you need to explicitly add the dependency for the target platform:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"You can add as many platform variants as needed.\n"
"The extension detects available libraries at build time and logs which variants were found."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "Excluding the automatic dependency (Maven)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "If you want full control over which native library variants are included, you can exclude the automatic selection and list them explicitly:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"If you exclude the automatic dependency, you **must** provide at least one platform variant manually.\n"
"The server will fail to start if no native QUIC library is found on the classpath."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "Adding the native QUIC dependency (Gradle)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"Gradle does not support Maven profile activation, so the native QUIC library is **not** selected automatically.\n"
"You must always add the dependency for your target platform(s) explicitly:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"If you build and deploy on the same platform, add only that platform's classifier.\n"
"If you build on one platform but deploy to another, add both:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "How it works"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "Same port, dual transport"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"The Quarkus HTTP server listens on the HTTPS port (default `8443`) for both TCP (HTTP/1.1, HTTP/2) and UDP (HTTP/3 over QUIC) traffic.\n"
"There is no separate port for HTTP/3."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "Alt-Svc discovery"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "When HTTP/3 is enabled, the server automatically adds an `Alt-Svc` header to HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 responses:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "Alt-Svc: h3=\":8443\"; ma=86400"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"This tells clients that HTTP/3 is available on the same port.\n"
"Browsers and HTTP clients that support HTTP/3 will upgrade to QUIC for subsequent requests."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "To disable the `Alt-Svc` header:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid "Transparent to application code"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/http3-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"HTTP/3 does not change how you write application code.\n"
"The same Jakarta REST resources, Vert.x routes, filters, and interceptors work across all HTTP versions.\n"
"You can check the protocol version of a request using `HttpServerRequest.version()` if needed."
msgstr ""

